  "text": "Last but not least, we are convinced that the present trade patterns and economic consensus based of Ricardian economics and free trade-whereby the best option for a country exporting bananas is to stick to its competitive advantage by keeping exporting bananas-are in fact a recipe to keep the poor countries poor. Exchanging raw material against finished goods has never made countries rich [CITATION_1] .",
